1
00:00:35,940 --> 00:00:38,720
=Angels and Guards=

2
00:00:38,720 --> 00:00:41,220
=Episode 10=

3
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:42,458
Come on. Are you taking it or not?

4
00:00:42,458 --> 00:00:43,083
Hurry up.

5
00:00:43,666 --> 00:00:44,250
Are you playing or not?

6
00:00:44,250 --> 00:00:45,541
Wait. Bomb.

7
00:00:45,541 --> 00:00:46,541
What...

8
00:00:47,916 --> 00:00:48,958
What luck.

9
00:00:50,083 --> 00:00:50,875
Double it.

10
00:00:52,125 --> 00:00:52,750
Why are you here?

11
00:00:52,916 --> 00:00:54,916
You never left Chong'er Pavilion
all night?

12
00:00:55,708 --> 00:00:57,458
Does a bathroom break count?

13
00:00:59,875 --> 00:01:00,666
Miss Shen.

14
00:01:01,375 --> 00:01:02,166
What happened?

15
00:01:02,875 --> 00:01:03,708
We can testify.

16
00:01:04,291 --> 00:01:04,708
That's right.

17
00:01:04,958 --> 00:01:06,583
Chang was playing cards
with us all night.

18
00:01:09,916 --> 00:01:11,583
I even won a thousand taels.

19
00:01:11,890 --> 00:01:12,680
(Great Ming Treasure Note)

20
00:01:16,166 --> 00:01:16,666
Nothing.

21
00:01:17,166 --> 00:01:17,708
Carry on.

22
00:01:19,875 --> 00:01:20,458
Miss Shen.

23
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:21,916
Go on. Come on.

24
00:01:22,708 --> 00:01:23,541
Pay up first.

25
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:24,291
It doubled.

26
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:26,541
(Maybe I'm overthinking it.)

27
00:01:27,375 --> 00:01:28,541
(Chang Beiming is not short on money.)

28
00:01:29,208 --> 00:01:30,541
(Why would he risk becoming a thief?)

29
00:01:31,375 --> 00:01:31,958
(But)

30
00:01:32,416 --> 00:01:33,791
(I still feel he and Feng Fuliu)

31
00:01:33,791 --> 00:01:34,833
(have something in common.)

32
00:01:35,250 --> 00:01:35,666
(And)

33
00:01:36,166 --> 00:01:36,708
(Mr. Lu)

34
00:01:36,958 --> 00:01:37,666
(and Marquis Taiping.)

35
00:01:38,083 --> 00:01:39,208
(Why do they both fear him?)

36
00:01:39,541 --> 00:01:40,791
(Northern Bureau)
How many times have I told you?

37
00:01:41,166 --> 00:01:42,166
Don't act rashly.

38
00:01:42,166 --> 00:01:43,083
Don't act rashly.

39
00:01:43,375 --> 00:01:44,875
Are you ignoring your superiors?

40
00:01:45,666 --> 00:01:46,708
No respect for authority.

41
00:01:47,333 --> 00:01:48,250
What punishment do you deserve?

42
00:01:49,583 --> 00:01:50,166
We...

43
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:52,083
Mr. Lu,

44
00:01:52,541 --> 00:01:54,458
the three of us went shopping last night

45
00:01:54,666 --> 00:01:55,708
and ran into the chivalrous thief
Feng Fuliu.

46
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:56,333
What?

47
00:01:57,333 --> 00:01:58,333
Phan...

48
00:01:58,416 --> 00:01:59,541
Phantom thief Feng Fuliu.

49
00:02:00,375 --> 00:02:02,708
How could we ignore a thief
right in front of us?

50
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:04,583
Shopping and passing by?

51
00:02:05,583 --> 00:02:06,333
Are you

52
00:02:06,333 --> 00:02:07,375
treating Mr. Zhang

53
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:09,208
like a three-year-old?

54
00:02:09,666 --> 00:02:10,958
Who goes shopping that late?

55
00:02:11,083 --> 00:02:11,833
Passing by what?

56
00:02:12,416 --> 00:02:13,583
Who has time during the day?

57
00:02:15,833 --> 00:02:16,500
Excuses.

58
00:02:17,041 --> 00:02:17,833
Nothing but excuses.

59
00:02:19,333 --> 00:02:21,500
My lord, she is clearly making excuses.

60
00:02:21,833 --> 00:02:22,500
Guokai,

61
00:02:22,916 --> 00:02:24,541
didn't they just say it?

62
00:02:26,291 --> 00:02:28,375
Whether they happened to meet him
on the street

63
00:02:28,583 --> 00:02:29,833
or happened to meet him elsewhere,

64
00:02:30,041 --> 00:02:31,833
in short, all in all,

65
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:34,416
they didn't interfere, did they?

66
00:02:35,583 --> 00:02:37,208
My lord, if you keep covering for them,

67
00:02:37,375 --> 00:02:38,291
they will only get more out of line.

68
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:39,583
That's not true.

69
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:41,208
With you here keeping them in line,

70
00:02:41,458 --> 00:02:42,041
that won't happen.

71
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:49,666
My eyes are injured,

72
00:02:50,208 --> 00:02:52,000
so I will skip the formal salute.

73
00:02:53,125 --> 00:02:54,583
It's fine.

74
00:02:55,208 --> 00:02:55,875
Duoyu,

75
00:02:56,500 --> 00:02:57,875
how is her injury?

76
00:02:58,125 --> 00:02:58,625
My lord,

77
00:02:59,083 --> 00:03:00,250
it is only a scrape on the eyelid.

78
00:03:00,541 --> 00:03:01,166
Nothing serious.

79
00:03:04,166 --> 00:03:06,541
Then may I

80
00:03:06,958 --> 00:03:09,583
skip training for the next few days?

81
00:03:09,625 --> 00:03:10,375
Of course.

82
00:03:10,625 --> 00:03:12,916
You may skip training
for the next few days.

83
00:03:12,916 --> 00:03:13,541
My lord.

84
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:15,875
If you keep this up,
I will never keep them in line.

85
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:16,916
Guokai.

86
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:19,208
You need to open your mind.

87
00:03:21,833 --> 00:03:22,500
Go rest.

88
00:03:25,770 --> 00:03:26,333
(Ministry of Justice)

89
00:03:26,333 --> 00:03:27,375
(Ministry of Justice)
Guan Yunfeng.

90
00:03:27,625 --> 00:03:29,166
Duke Wei

91
00:03:29,208 --> 00:03:32,500
is a descendant of General Xu Da,
Prince Zhongshan.

92
00:03:32,708 --> 00:03:33,708
The Azure Dragon Jade

93
00:03:33,916 --> 00:03:36,791
is a family heirloom bestowed
by the Hongwu Emperor.

94
00:03:36,875 --> 00:03:38,750
You will be the death of me!

95
00:03:40,970 --> 00:03:42,850
(Ministry of Justice)

96
00:03:43,291 --> 00:03:43,916
Come on.

97
00:03:44,250 --> 00:03:45,750
Feng. Feng.

98
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:46,500
Are you all right, Feng?

99
00:03:48,916 --> 00:03:49,458
I'm fine.

100
00:03:50,666 --> 00:03:53,333
Feng, we all know you did your best.

101
00:03:53,666 --> 00:03:55,000
We are just unlucky.

102
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:56,708
The criminals we run into

103
00:03:56,708 --> 00:03:57,833
are always at the top
of the Bounty List.

104
00:03:57,833 --> 00:03:58,625
Drop it. Drop it.

105
00:03:59,416 --> 00:04:01,833
Feng, let's buy you a drink.

106
00:04:01,916 --> 00:04:02,375
A drink?

107
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:02,916
Yes, a drink.

108
00:04:03,166 --> 00:04:04,208
At Chong'er Pavilion.

109
00:04:04,833 --> 00:04:05,583
(Chong'er Pavilion)
We drink until we drop.

110
00:04:05,666 --> 00:04:06,333
That's right.

111
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:06,833
Let's go.

112
00:04:06,833 --> 00:04:07,750
The wine at Chong'er Pavilion

113
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:08,458
is excellent.

114
00:04:08,458 --> 00:04:09,541
I have heard so much about it.

115
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:10,625
Exactly.

116
00:04:11,875 --> 00:04:12,916
What are you doing here?

117
00:04:13,083 --> 00:04:13,833
Untidy clothes.

118
00:04:13,958 --> 00:04:14,750
Not handsome.

119
00:04:15,083 --> 00:04:16,000
Vulgar rich men.

120
00:04:16,291 --> 00:04:17,083
We don't serve your kind.

121
00:04:17,083 --> 00:04:18,125
How am I not handsome?

122
00:04:18,375 --> 00:04:18,833
Exactly.

123
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:19,708
What do you mean, not handsome?

124
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:20,583
Forget it.

125
00:04:21,541 --> 00:04:21,958
Let's go.

126
00:04:21,958 --> 00:04:22,708
Feng.

127
00:04:22,708 --> 00:04:23,083
Feng.

128
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:25,750
Constable Guan.

129
00:04:26,541 --> 00:04:27,125
Constable Guan.

130
00:04:27,958 --> 00:04:29,500
Our female Jinyiwei's quarters
are in the back courtyard.

131
00:04:30,083 --> 00:04:32,291
Tell me whatever you
and your men want to eat.

132
00:04:34,208 --> 00:04:34,708
Good.

133
00:04:36,541 --> 00:04:37,166
So good.

134
00:04:38,791 --> 00:04:39,541
What is good?

135
00:04:41,708 --> 00:04:42,500
I mean,

136
00:04:43,208 --> 00:04:45,125
today's wine and meat

137
00:04:45,541 --> 00:04:46,166
are on me.

138
00:04:46,166 --> 00:04:47,375
Thank you, Feng!

139
00:04:47,958 --> 00:04:48,708
That's our brother, Feng.

140
00:04:48,750 --> 00:04:49,708
Always so generous.

141
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:50,666
Fill them up.

142
00:04:52,666 --> 00:04:53,250
Constable Guan.

143
00:04:54,083 --> 00:04:56,291
You seem troubled.

144
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:57,458
Did something happen?

145
00:04:58,666 --> 00:04:59,041
Wait.

146
00:04:59,333 --> 00:04:59,666
Hold on.

147
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:00,708
Young Master Chang.

148
00:05:01,541 --> 00:05:02,458
Isn't that Miss Shen?

149
00:05:03,916 --> 00:05:04,375
Come here.

150
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:06,416
It is all that phantom thief
Feng Fuliu's fault.

151
00:05:06,875 --> 00:05:07,791
Feng Fuliu

152
00:05:08,416 --> 00:05:09,916
has ruined our Enforcement Division.

153
00:05:12,041 --> 00:05:13,166
I, Guan, swear today

154
00:05:13,625 --> 00:05:14,583
that if I fail to catch Feng Fuliu,

155
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,041
I will never take a wife.

156
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:17,583
Well said, Feng!

157
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:22,125
Then you are destined to die a bachelor.

158
00:05:24,875 --> 00:05:25,416
Who are you?

159
00:05:26,666 --> 00:05:27,833
Why are you defending Feng Fuliu?

160
00:05:28,458 --> 00:05:29,291
Who am I?

161
00:05:29,958 --> 00:05:31,416
The owner of Chong'er Pavilion.

162
00:05:34,041 --> 00:05:35,708
Young Master Chang himself.

163
00:05:36,541 --> 00:05:38,500
You say I'm defending Feng Fuliu?

164
00:05:39,541 --> 00:05:41,541
Do you know what kind of man
Feng Fuliu is?

165
00:05:42,250 --> 00:05:46,708
A peerless phantom thief
ranked second on the Bounty List.

166
00:05:47,625 --> 00:05:48,708
You rookies

167
00:05:48,958 --> 00:05:51,375
think you can catch Feng Fuliu?

168
00:05:52,250 --> 00:05:52,833
Isn't that laughable?

169
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:53,791
Very laughable.

170
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:55,458
At least

171
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:58,291
Constable Guan has a heart for justice.

172
00:05:58,875 --> 00:05:59,750
Unlike some people,

173
00:06:00,416 --> 00:06:01,416
who cannot tell right from wrong

174
00:06:01,708 --> 00:06:02,791
and only know how to run their mouths.

175
00:06:05,166 --> 00:06:05,958
You...

176
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:08,083
You are taking his side against me?

177
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:11,875
Fine.

178
00:06:13,375 --> 00:06:15,041
If he can catch Feng Fuliu,

179
00:06:15,791 --> 00:06:18,750
I will carry a cauldron from Chong'er
to the imperial city.

180
00:06:19,875 --> 00:06:21,000
If he can't,

181
00:06:22,583 --> 00:06:25,125
you will serve me like a slave
for the rest of your life.

182
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,500
Fine. Bet accepted.

183
00:06:30,958 --> 00:06:31,500
Bingfan,

184
00:06:32,250 --> 00:06:33,541
this bet is far too unfair to you.

185
00:06:34,041 --> 00:06:34,541
It is fine.

186
00:06:35,625 --> 00:06:37,208
Constable Guan, I believe in you.

187
00:06:37,208 --> 00:06:38,708
You can surely capture Feng Fuliu alive.

188
00:06:39,666 --> 00:06:41,416
I will catch him,
even if it costs me my life.

189
00:06:51,291 --> 00:06:51,833
Go, go.

190
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:52,583
That owner...

191
00:07:00,416 --> 00:07:01,166
Duoyu.

192
00:07:01,708 --> 00:07:02,458
That night,

193
00:07:02,583 --> 00:07:04,791
why did you suddenly appear
beneath the city wall?

194
00:07:07,791 --> 00:07:09,916
I was worried about you,
so I followed you.

195
00:07:12,125 --> 00:07:13,291
You...

196
00:07:13,916 --> 00:07:16,375
You are no ordinary servant.

197
00:07:18,208 --> 00:07:19,166
(Chong'er Pavilion)
Let's go there.

198
00:07:19,291 --> 00:07:20,333
- Sure.
- My treat today.

199
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:21,750
Why is that constable standing there?

200
00:07:22,125 --> 00:07:22,833
No idea.

201
00:07:23,291 --> 00:07:23,666
Is he all right?

202
00:07:23,666 --> 00:07:24,541
Leave him. Let's go.

203
00:07:25,625 --> 00:07:26,750
What is that constable doing there?

204
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:27,333
Go, go.

205
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:32,083
Bingfan.

206
00:07:32,541 --> 00:07:33,083
I'm coming.

207
00:07:44,250 --> 00:07:44,875
Excellent blade work.

208
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:48,791
Constable Guan.

209
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:50,541
Are you here on a case?

210
00:07:53,291 --> 00:07:53,708
No.

211
00:07:55,791 --> 00:07:56,708
My mother said

212
00:07:57,833 --> 00:07:58,833
that before seeing a lady,

213
00:07:59,083 --> 00:08:00,625
a man should show his best side.

214
00:08:01,541 --> 00:08:03,916
This uniform is the best thing I own.

215
00:08:07,291 --> 00:08:08,000
Did you need something?

216
00:08:13,666 --> 00:08:14,500
What does this mean?

217
00:08:16,166 --> 00:08:18,750
These handcuffs are forged
from fine steel.

218
00:08:19,541 --> 00:08:21,166
My father passed them down to me
when he was a constable.

219
00:08:21,375 --> 00:08:23,250
No blade or famous sword
can cut through them.

220
00:08:23,333 --> 00:08:24,625
For arrests, cases,

221
00:08:24,875 --> 00:08:26,583
and catching thieves, they are essential.

222
00:08:27,041 --> 00:08:28,000
You can't buy these anywhere.

223
00:08:30,083 --> 00:08:31,208
Are you trying to sell them to me?

224
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:32,333
No.

225
00:08:34,208 --> 00:08:35,375
I want to give them to you.

226
00:08:35,833 --> 00:08:36,583
From now on, when you catch thieves,

227
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,041
clap these on them,
and they will never escape.

228
00:08:41,583 --> 00:08:42,208
Give them to me?

229
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:44,625
Why give me something so precious?

230
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:46,833
I...

231
00:08:48,541 --> 00:08:48,916
Well...

232
00:08:49,625 --> 00:08:50,541
Just take them.

233
00:08:52,416 --> 00:08:54,166
If I take them, what will you use?

234
00:08:55,666 --> 00:08:56,291
It's fine.

235
00:08:56,958 --> 00:08:58,208
They are yours. Keep them.

236
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:04,333
What are you laughing at?

237
00:09:04,750 --> 00:09:05,916
Why were you eavesdropping?

238
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:07,625
I didn't mean to.

239
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:09,833
I only came out to cool off.

240
00:09:10,583 --> 00:09:11,333
But

241
00:09:13,541 --> 00:09:15,166
I really couldn't help it.

242
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:17,166
Cool off?

243
00:09:17,375 --> 00:09:18,541
You came out of your room.

244
00:09:18,708 --> 00:09:19,708
You were clearly eavesdropping.

245
00:09:20,208 --> 00:09:20,875
This is

246
00:09:20,875 --> 00:09:23,125
the first time in my life
I have seen a man court a girl

247
00:09:24,541 --> 00:09:25,500
by giving her handcuffs.

248
00:09:28,916 --> 00:09:29,791
Don't talk nonsense.

249
00:09:31,083 --> 00:09:31,750
We have

250
00:09:35,458 --> 00:09:36,375
a professional friendship.

251
00:09:39,875 --> 00:09:40,625
Chang Beiming,

252
00:09:41,166 --> 00:09:42,541
nothing decent ever comes out
of your mouth.

253
00:09:42,958 --> 00:09:44,541
Constable Guan and I are not like that.

254
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:47,458
Look at him.

255
00:09:47,666 --> 00:09:49,041
The way he dressed today,

256
00:09:49,458 --> 00:09:50,541
everything he just said,

257
00:09:50,875 --> 00:09:52,083
and these ridiculous handcuffs.

258
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:54,958
Who would believe
he doesn't mean it that way?

259
00:09:56,875 --> 00:10:00,000
You have the dirtiest mind
in all of Chong'er Pavilion.

260
00:10:05,458 --> 00:10:07,166
Constable Guan,
I will accept these handcuffs.

261
00:10:07,708 --> 00:10:08,708
I will use them

262
00:10:09,208 --> 00:10:10,791
to catch more notorious thieves.

263
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:12,916
I won't let your fine gift
go to waste.

264
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,750
Yeah! Yeah!

265
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:23,708
Excellent!

266
00:10:24,041 --> 00:10:25,875
Bingfan accepted them!

267
00:10:27,625 --> 00:10:29,291
Bingfan accepted them!

268
00:10:31,083 --> 00:10:32,500
He gave me a gift.

269
00:10:33,083 --> 00:10:34,125
Why is he

270
00:10:35,208 --> 00:10:36,416
happier than I am that I accepted it?

271
00:10:36,750 --> 00:10:37,375
How should I know?

272
00:10:40,166 --> 00:10:40,500
What...

273
00:10:41,125 --> 00:10:42,291
What is he angry about?

274
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:45,291
You men are all so strange.

275
00:10:46,250 --> 00:10:46,833
Hua.

276
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:49,666
I heard Feng Fuliu hurt you yesterday.

277
00:10:50,041 --> 00:10:50,583
Are you all right?

278
00:10:55,208 --> 00:10:57,458
Thank you for your concern,
Young Master Chang.

279
00:10:57,958 --> 00:10:59,500
What does Feng Fuliu look like?

280
00:11:00,208 --> 00:11:01,750
Is he handsome? Tell me.

281
00:11:05,458 --> 00:11:07,083
I really didn't see clearly.

282
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:08,000
I'm going back.

283
00:11:15,541 --> 00:11:16,958
The spring wind dares
to brush the willows.

284
00:11:18,625 --> 00:11:19,125
What?

285
00:11:23,125 --> 00:11:23,708
Nothing.

286
00:11:24,625 --> 00:11:25,458
Good night, Young Master Chang.

287
00:11:47,458 --> 00:11:48,333
Why are you here?

288
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:49,750
Bingfan.

289
00:11:53,041 --> 00:11:54,125
I wanted to see you.

290
00:11:54,791 --> 00:11:56,500
The food at Chong'er Pavilion
is too expensive.

291
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:57,666
So I begged the attendants.

292
00:11:58,041 --> 00:11:58,583
They said

293
00:11:58,958 --> 00:12:00,083
if I wash dishes here
for free every day,

294
00:12:00,291 --> 00:12:01,375
I can come to the back courtyard
to see you.

295
00:12:01,875 --> 00:12:02,958
That is bullying.

296
00:12:03,625 --> 00:12:04,458
I will go talk to Chang Beiming.

297
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:06,750
It's fine.

298
00:12:07,791 --> 00:12:08,708
I actually enjoy it.

299
00:12:09,166 --> 00:12:11,208
Besides, last time I treated everyone
at Chong'er Pavilion,

300
00:12:11,458 --> 00:12:13,000
I spent all my money
and still owed a debt.

301
00:12:13,416 --> 00:12:14,375
Young Master Chang didn't make a fuss.

302
00:12:15,333 --> 00:12:17,250
I will wash dishes for free
to pay off the debts.

303
00:12:19,333 --> 00:12:19,916
Then I will help you.

304
00:12:33,291 --> 00:12:33,833
Take these back.

305
00:12:35,875 --> 00:12:36,333
Why?

306
00:12:37,375 --> 00:12:39,333
They are your family heirloom.
I can't accept them.

307
00:12:40,666 --> 00:12:41,791
A gift once given

308
00:12:42,416 --> 00:12:43,291
should never be taken back.

309
00:12:44,166 --> 00:12:44,958
If you don't like them,

310
00:12:45,916 --> 00:12:46,625
throw them away.

311
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:52,810
(Chong'er Pavilion)

312
00:12:55,541 --> 00:12:58,583
From now on, anyone in official uniform
is banned from Chong'er Pavilion.

313
00:12:58,916 --> 00:12:59,500
Then I will take it off.

314
00:12:59,916 --> 00:13:01,916
Untidy clothing is forbidden.

315
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:03,333
That has always been the rule.

316
00:13:03,791 --> 00:13:05,083
You are clearly targeting me.

317
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,500
I am. What about it?

318
00:13:14,041 --> 00:13:15,583
Chang Shuai, Chang Jun. See him out.

319
00:13:16,791 --> 00:13:17,208
You...

320
00:13:26,166 --> 00:13:27,291
Guan Yunfeng.

321
00:13:27,625 --> 00:13:29,833
Why wash dishes of all things?

322
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,416
Why are you washing dishes here?

323
00:13:47,916 --> 00:13:48,666
Lost a bet?

324
00:13:50,125 --> 00:13:51,458
We are short-handed today.

325
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:52,666
Come help.

326
00:13:54,125 --> 00:13:54,500
All right.

327
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:56,291
So shiny.

328
00:14:10,416 --> 00:14:10,791
Hey.

329
00:14:10,916 --> 00:14:12,083
This is how you wash dishes?

330
00:14:14,666 --> 00:14:16,125
Rinse them twice in salt water first,

331
00:14:16,916 --> 00:14:18,416
then twice in clean water.

332
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:19,708
That is the only way to get them clean.

333
00:14:20,083 --> 00:14:21,875
Otherwise, the guests
will get upset stomachs.

334
00:14:31,666 --> 00:14:33,000
Like this. Watch.

335
00:14:36,458 --> 00:14:37,666
See? Nice and shiny.

336
00:14:50,666 --> 00:14:51,416
Don't get mad.

337
00:14:51,875 --> 00:14:52,833
I will stop teaching.

338
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:05,270
(Scar Balm)

339
00:15:05,791 --> 00:15:06,416
Scar Balm.

340
00:15:07,166 --> 00:15:08,291
It treats scars on the body.

341
00:15:11,541 --> 00:15:12,000
Take it.

342
00:15:15,270 --> 00:15:17,060
(Scar Balm)

343
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:18,166
Thank you.

344
00:15:18,666 --> 00:15:19,291
Now wash the dishes.

345
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:23,850
(Imperial Edict)

346
00:15:24,625 --> 00:15:25,583
Duke Wei

347
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:27,916
lost an imperial treasure.

348
00:15:28,416 --> 00:15:30,416
He filed a petition before His Majesty,

349
00:15:30,791 --> 00:15:31,958
requesting the Jinyiwei

350
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:34,333
to capture the phantom thief.

351
00:15:35,208 --> 00:15:35,875
(Northern Bureau)
This time,

352
00:15:36,625 --> 00:15:38,250
we are acting by imperial order
to capture Feng Fuliu.

353
00:15:38,958 --> 00:15:39,875
We must

354
00:15:40,416 --> 00:15:41,208
catch him with ease

355
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:43,000
and show the Cabinet,

356
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:46,166
the Six Ministries, and the Commander

357
00:15:46,958 --> 00:15:47,833
that the Jinyiwei are no pushovers.

358
00:15:48,375 --> 00:15:48,875
Yes, my lord.

359
00:15:49,875 --> 00:15:50,541
Advisor Dong,

360
00:15:50,875 --> 00:15:53,083
go draw up a flawless plan

361
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:54,333
to trap Feng Fuliu.

362
00:15:54,916 --> 00:15:55,583
This time,

363
00:15:56,916 --> 00:15:59,291
I will personally oversee the arrest.

364
00:15:59,458 --> 00:15:59,708
Yes, my lord.

365
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:00,458
Commissioner.

366
00:16:01,083 --> 00:16:03,541
This time, we use only male Jinyiwei,
not the female ones, right?

367
00:16:04,125 --> 00:16:04,583
Of course.

368
00:16:04,666 --> 00:16:05,708
Those three

369
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:07,250
will only drag us down.

370
00:16:07,708 --> 00:16:09,916
This time, I want the male Jinyiwei

371
00:16:10,833 --> 00:16:11,625
to take all the credit.

372
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:12,958
Yes, my lord.

373
00:16:13,916 --> 00:16:14,750
Capture Feng Fuliu?

374
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:16,625
Lu Guokai won't let us join?

375
00:16:16,958 --> 00:16:17,250
Correct.

376
00:16:17,791 --> 00:16:18,958
This time, he has gathered
all six Qianhu,

377
00:16:19,250 --> 00:16:19,791
twelve Baihu,

378
00:16:20,291 --> 00:16:21,750
and every skilled fighter he can find.

379
00:16:22,625 --> 00:16:23,208
Only

380
00:16:23,708 --> 00:16:24,750
you female Jinyiwei were left out.

381
00:16:26,125 --> 00:16:27,000
Outrageous.

382
00:16:27,833 --> 00:16:29,541
Feng Fuliu is highly skilled
at disguising.

383
00:16:29,958 --> 00:16:32,250
When the time comes,
we will have the advisor set a password.

384
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:34,083
Greetings, Commissioner.

385
00:16:35,166 --> 00:16:35,958
Who let you in?

386
00:16:36,375 --> 00:16:37,583
No one was guarding the door.

387
00:16:38,125 --> 00:16:38,916
So I came in.

388
00:16:38,958 --> 00:16:39,500
What is it?

389
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,500
I request permission
to capture Feng Fuliu.

390
00:16:43,958 --> 00:16:44,583
This matter

391
00:16:44,916 --> 00:16:45,833
is already under my command.

392
00:16:46,625 --> 00:16:47,291
You were not summoned.

393
00:16:48,041 --> 00:16:48,791
Don't make trouble here.

394
00:16:48,958 --> 00:16:50,500
I have fought Feng Fuliu before.

395
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:52,125
I know a little about him.

396
00:16:52,291 --> 00:16:52,916
Please...

397
00:16:52,916 --> 00:16:53,416
Shen Bingfan.

398
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:56,958
Deploying officers is my job
as Commissioner.

399
00:16:57,375 --> 00:16:58,583
You are a mere low-ranking Squad Leader,

400
00:16:58,583 --> 00:16:59,708
yet you want a say in our strategy?

401
00:17:00,375 --> 00:17:02,666
Why do you keep refusing
to let the female guards join?

402
00:17:03,041 --> 00:17:04,375
Is this because of a personal grudge?

403
00:17:05,125 --> 00:17:07,958
Shen Bingfan, you defied
and insulted your superior.

404
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:09,541
Advisor.

405
00:17:10,583 --> 00:17:11,291
Put it on record.

406
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,166
Suspend her for ten days.

407
00:17:13,416 --> 00:17:14,041
Mr. Lu.

408
00:17:14,208 --> 00:17:15,833
What? Is that not enough?

409
00:17:16,416 --> 00:17:16,916
Dismissed!

410
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:22,750
Suspended? So be it.

411
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:23,875
At least we can go shopping together.

412
00:17:24,416 --> 00:17:24,958
Let's check this place.

413
00:17:25,708 --> 00:17:27,250
Exactly. A rare bit of free time.

414
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,166
If a fool like Lu Guokai

415
00:17:29,375 --> 00:17:31,041
can catch Feng Fuliu,

416
00:17:31,291 --> 00:17:33,041
I'll eat my hat.

417
00:17:33,750 --> 00:17:34,375
True.

418
00:17:34,875 --> 00:17:35,708
With Lu Guokai,

419
00:17:36,291 --> 00:17:37,500
there is no way he can catch Feng Fuliu.

420
00:17:38,583 --> 00:17:39,750
When the male Jinyiwei fail,

421
00:17:40,125 --> 00:17:41,541
it won't be too late for us to shine.

422
00:17:46,083 --> 00:17:46,500
Hua,

423
00:17:47,083 --> 00:17:48,416
is this one of those

424
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:49,583
Nanyang imports?

425
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:52,833
Yes.

426
00:17:53,125 --> 00:17:53,916
This is nice.

427
00:17:54,083 --> 00:17:54,500
Smell it.

428
00:17:54,875 --> 00:17:55,333
Sir.

429
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:57,208
What fragrance powder is this?

430
00:17:57,208 --> 00:17:58,875
This is a special fragrance powder

431
00:17:58,958 --> 00:17:59,958
called Soul-Stealing Fragrance.

432
00:18:09,875 --> 00:18:10,833
(Constable Guan, are you all right?)

433
00:18:11,083 --> 00:18:11,416
(I'm fine.)

434
00:18:17,416 --> 00:18:17,750
Bingfan.

435
00:18:17,875 --> 00:18:19,208
Smell this. Does it seem familiar?

436
00:18:24,666 --> 00:18:26,583
Isn't this the same scent
from the fragrance powder

437
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:28,750
scattered on the ground
when we fought Diaotu?

438
00:18:45,020 --> 00:18:48,190
♪Because you once entered my dreams♪

439
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:51,940
♪Truth and illusion blur in wine♪

440
00:18:52,190 --> 00:18:55,190
♪My heart drifted lost♪

441
00:18:55,190 --> 00:18:58,600
♪Yet found you in the crowd♪

442
00:18:59,690 --> 00:19:02,900
♪My blood still burns
as the world surges♪

443
00:19:03,310 --> 00:19:06,650
♪The land is fair, and you are free♪

444
00:19:07,230 --> 00:19:09,440
♪Sword drawn, lost in obsession♪

445
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:13,480
♪I've softly let it go♪

446
00:19:13,480 --> 00:19:17,350
♪The vow you made was true♪

447
00:19:17,350 --> 00:19:21,100
♪Yet like clouds, it stops for no one♪

448
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:23,310
♪Put away those dreamlike words♪

449
00:19:23,310 --> 00:19:27,850
♪And forget at world's end♪

450
00:19:28,150 --> 00:19:29,650
♪Embracing memory♪

451
00:19:29,650 --> 00:19:32,020
♪Through blossoms and dreams♪

452
00:19:32,020 --> 00:19:35,900
♪You hide in the crowd, silent♪

453
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:38,230
♪I wish to let it pass♪

454
00:19:38,230 --> 00:19:43,230
♪And run toward this vast life♪

